<title>
Time Lag Test
</title>
<ptxt>
This test is to check conditions of clutch, brake and fluid pressure. “Time lag” means time elapsed since select lever is shifted with engine idling till shock is felt.
</ptxt>
<s1>
<ptxt>
With chocks placed before and behind front and rear wheels respectively, depress brake pedal.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Start engine.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
With a stopwatch ready, shift select lever from “N” to “D” range and measure time from that moment till shock is felt.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Similarly measure time lag by shifting select lever from “N” to “R” range.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Gear shifting time lag
</title>
<ptxt>
“N” → “D”: Less than 0.9 sec.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
“N” → “R”: Less than 1.2 sec.
</ptxt>
</spec>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
When repeating this test, be sure to wait at least one minute after select lever is shifted back to “N” range.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Engine should be warmed up fully for this test.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Repeat test 3 times and take average of those data for final time lag data.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
</s1>
